    "To render samples aggregated along a given ray, Mildenhall et al. (2021) proposes Eq. 1 where the exponent represents the accumulated transmittance w.r.t to the volumetric density of preceding samples.",
    "In practice, Eq. 1 is numerically approximated using quadrature, in Eq.",
    "2, where δ i is the thickness of a volume sample along a line segment.",
    "Subsequently, a loss function L(C *, Ĉ) is used to optimise the predicted ray color w.r.t to the color of a ground truth pixel, C *.",
    "To reduce the influence from spectral bias (Rahaman et al. 2019) the NeRF maps position and viewing directions to a view-point's fourier features, using the encoding γ in Eq. 3, where k is a hyper-parameter defining the dimensionality of the feature vector (the bandwidth of our discretized frequency encoding)."
  ],
